<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id5b69bb30-3a70-11f1-8704-e0e66b400d7c" identifier="/us/usc/t29/s2634"><num value="2634">§ 2634.</num><heading> Compensation</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id5b69bb31-3a70-11f1-8704-e0e66b400d7c" identifier="/us/usc/t29/s2634/a"><num value="a" class="bold">(a)</num><heading class="bold"> Pay</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Members of the Commission shall serve without compensation.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id5b69bb32-3a70-11f1-8704-e0e66b400d7c" identifier="/us/usc/t29/s2634/b"><num value="b" class="bold">(b)</num><heading class="bold"> Travel expenses</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Members of the Commission shall be allowed reasonable travel expenses, including a per diem allowance, in accordance with <ref href="/us/usc/t5/s5703">section 5703 of title 5</ref> when performing duties of the Commission.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="id5b69bb33-3a70-11f1-8704-e0e66b400d7c">(<ref href="/us/pl/103/3/tIII/s304">Pub. L. 103–3, title III, § 304</ref>, <date date="1993-02-05">Feb. 5, 1993</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/107/25">107 Stat. 25</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
